[size=6][b]Modules[/b][/size]

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BellCubeDev/AdditionalClockwork/latest/Images/SwellSorting.png[/img]
[size=3]Takes advantage of [url=https://skse.silverlock.org]SKSE[/url] and [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/22854]powerofthree's Papyrus Extender[/url] to enhance Clockwork's sorting system FAR beyond what we are used to! No longer are we bound by the days when every mod requires a new patch, and long-gone are the times when you had to sort out your potions, books, or equipment![/size]
[size=1]For a deeper look into the technical stuff, see [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/articles/3232]the dedicated article[/url]. Alternatively, if you can read Ppayrus, you can also look at the [url=https://github.com/BellCubeDev/AdditionalClockwork/blob/latest/dist/Modules/SKSE/EnhancedSorting/source/scripts/CLWA_SKSE_Sorting.psc]source code[/url].[/size]

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BellCubeDev/AdditionalClockwork/latest/Images/BugFixes.png[/img]
[size=3]Fixes many bugs in Clockwork, like the numerous positioning fixes, some Havok Havoc (when the physics engine throws a fit), children and spouses not using furniture, and, most importantly, the Courier issue. Rain or shine, GET OFF MY LAWN![/size]
[size=1]For an in-depth technical look into my Courier Counterspell, see [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/articles/3232]the dedicated article[/url].[/size]

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BellCubeDev/AdditionalClockwork/latest/Images/ShadowmarksBanner.png[/img]
[size=4]Made of three modules, which each add "Guild" (Member) shadowmarks to these locations:
[/size][list]
[size=4][*][color=#ffd966]The Castle's front door[/color]
[*][color=#6d9eeb]The Travel Room's door to the Main Hall[/color]
[*][color=#93c47d]Each of the Terminus locations[/color] (two in Riften, one everywhere else)
[/size][/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BellCubeDev/AdditionalClockwork/latest/Images/WoodworkersWhim.png[/img]
[size=4]Adds two things: An Axe Mount to the Work Room and a script that searches for dropped/mounted axes nearby for you to chop wood with.

Really made up of three modules:
[list]
[*][color=#ffd966]The script enabled [b]globally[/b][/color][b] (does [u]NOT[/u] require Clockwork)[/b]
[*][color=#6d9eeb]The script enabled [b]ONLY in the Work Room[/b][/color] ([b][u]redundant[/u][/b] if the Global module is enabled)
[*][color=#93c47d]An Axe mount for the Work Room[/color]
[/list][/size]
[size=6][b]Minor Tweaks & Changes[/b][/size]
[size=2]Now with even less impact on gameplay![/size][list][*][b][size=4][color=#6aa84f]Mausoleum Dummy Dor Fix[/color] - [/size][/b]When leaving Nurndural for the first time, there is a scene that plays with Lamashtu and Shadow. While the scene plays out, you are prevented from leaving by a fake door. However, this fake door, when disappears, is EXTREMELY NOTICEABLE if you look at the door. Of course, I had to fix this. My efficient brethren, you can rest easy now. (So long as you're not fixing the pipes right now, you should be fine for a mid-game install)
[*][b][size=4][color=#6aa84f]Clockwork Title Remover[/color] - [/size][/b]Removes the giant floating Clockwork title that appears when you first enter the Castle's valley [b]([url=https://forums.nexusmods.com/index.php?showtopic=10280988/#entry97162223]idea[/url] by [url=https://forums.nexusmods.com/index.php?/user/42417205-foamimi/]Foamimi[/url])[/b].
[/list]

[size=6][b]Integration, Patches, and Consistency
[/b][/size]You know. Standard patches etc.
[color=#ffd966][size=4][b]High Poly Project[/b]
[/size][/color][list][*][b][color=#6aa84f][size=4]Coals Fix:[/size][/color][/b][size=4] Uses High Poly Project's mesh for the coals instead of the vanilla mesh. [/size][size=2](See project images)[/size]
[*][size=4][b][color=#6aa84f]Hay Fix:[/color][/b] Fixes the hay [url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Z-fighting&oldid=1031681976#:~:text=z-fighting%2C%20also%20called%20stitching%20or%20planefighting%2C%20is%20a%20phenomenon%20in%203d%20rendering%20that%20occurs%20when%20two%20or%20more%20primitives%20have%20very%20similar%20distances%20to%20the%20camera.&text=this%20then%20means%20that%20when%20a%20specific%20pixel%20is%20being%20rendered%2C%20it%20is%20nearly%20random%20which%20one%20of%20the%20two%20primitives%20are%20drawn%20in%20that%20pixel]z-fighting[/url] that appears all throughout Clockwork Castle when using HPP's mesh.[/size][size=1][/size]
[size=1](Thankfully, Skyrim's rendering engine doesn't throw hissy fits when there's z-fighting. It just picks one and goes with it, thankfully. Thus, this is more of a small aesthetic change than a must-have like the Coals Fix)
[/size][/list]

